name: df-prf
params: setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, setvar s4, setvar s5
body: |- wceq(cprf, cmpo(s0, s1, universe, universe, csb(s2, cdm(cfv(c1st, cv(s0))), cop(cmpt(s3, cv(s2), cop(cfv(cfv(c1st, cv(s0)), cv(s3)), cfv(cfv(c1st, cv(s1)), cv(s3)))), cmpo(s3, s4, cv(s2), cv(s2), cmpt(s5, cdm(co(cv(s3), cfv(c2nd, cv(s0)), cv(s4))), cop(cfv(co(cv(s3), cfv(c2nd, cv(s0)), cv(s4)), cv(s5)), cfv(co(cv(s3), cfv(c2nd, cv(s1)), cv(s4)), cv(s5)))))))))
comment: Define the pairing operation for functors (which takes two functors ` F : C --> D ` and ` G : C --> E ` and produces ` ( F pairF G ) : C --> ( D Xc. E ) ` ). (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 11-Jan-2017.)
